# Rules

Project-specific non-negotiables the agent must follow on every turn. Loaded by the `context-loader` skill at the start of every session and injected into context.

Rules are dual-listed: things the agent must DO, things it must NOT do. Sharper than prose, easier to enforce per turn. Fill in below — delete the `(example)` bullets, write the rules that actually apply to your project.

## DO

- (example) Use env vars + `.gitignore` for all secrets
- (example) Default LLM calls to Haiku unless explicitly justified
- (example) Paginate every list endpoint (default limit 25)
- (example) Preserve EN/HU diacritics in strings: á é í ó ö ő ú ü ű

## DO NOT

- (example) No `SELECT *` in queries — specify columns
- (example) No inline base64 in source — static assets go to `public/` or object storage
- (example) Do not install alternative bundlers, CSS frameworks, or component libraries
- (example) Do not commit `.env`, credentials, or service-role keys

## Ordering invariants (project-specific)

If your project has hard ordering rules (X must happen before Y), name them here. The agent reads this section every session and will refuse to do step Y without step X — the same way the harness refuses to deploy on a failing verify. See `.harness/conventions.md` "Ordering invariants" for the pattern.

- (example) Run database migration before running seed scripts (seeds assume the schema exists)
- (example) Set up auth before adding any user-facing route (otherwise routes go live unauthenticated)
- (example) Provision the database project before requesting any third-party secrets (secrets are stored in the project's Edge Function secret store)

